'Rain' is the third single from Mika's second studio album The Boy Who Knew Too Much released in the United Kingdom. The song was produced and mixed by <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/Greg+Wells" class="bbcode_artist">Greg Wells</a> and features the violinist <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/Owen+Pallett" class="bbcode_artist">Owen Pallett</a>.

 &quot;Rain is an unapologetic '80s pop record. I bumped into producer <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/Stuart+Price" class="bbcode_artist">Stuart Price</a> while he was working with <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/The+Killers" class="bbcode_artist">The Killers</a> at Olympic Studios. He helped me program this. It reminded him of <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/ABBA" class="bbcode_artist">ABBA</a> and <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/Frankie+Goes+to+Hollywood" class="bbcode_artist">Frankie Goes to Hollywood</a>.&quot;

